window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>A man’s lifetime of secrets and lies. A woman on the hunt for his hidden riches. But there’s a sting in the tale in this gripping short story by the <i>New York Times</i> bestselling author of <i>We Lie Here</i>.</p> <p>Frankie is a caregiver facing a meager and thankless future. Until her elderly charge dies—but not before revealing his secret. It’s buried in Death Valley. Enough money to change Frankie’s life forever. All she has to do is follow his instructions and stay on the path, and her prayers will be answered. It’s everything Frankie hopes for. But nothing like she expects.</p> <p><i>Rachel Howzell Hall’s </i>Scorpions<i> is part of </i>Never Tell<i>, a heart-pounding collection of stories about secrets, lies, and mind games. They can be read or listened to in one sitting. Just keep the endings to yourself.</i></p>"; 
